OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F308A1751375570
OL,3,CPrisons minister: Legislation to ban
OL,4,Cmost short sentences due 'imminently'
OL,6,F"I can give you lots of facts - 55% of
OL,7,Fwomen in the justice system have drug
OL,8,Faddiction issues... Around 50% of
OL,9,Fwomen in prison have brain injuries,
OL,10,Foften as a result of domestic abuse.
OL,11,FSo we're dealing with some very, very
OL,12,Fcomplex people and often some very ill
OL,13,Fpeople."
OL,15,FThe minister said he still believes
OL,16,Fwomen's justice needs radical reform,
OL,17,Fand that the Women's Justice Board, an
OL,18,Fexpert panel commissioned by the
OL,19,Fgovernment to overhaul how female
OL,20,Foffenders are treated, will implement
OL,21,F"radical" changes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
