OL,3,CPrisons minister: Legislation to ban
OL,4,Cmost short sentences due 'imminently'
OL,6,F75% of women in prison were there
OL,7,Funder 12 months at the end of last
OL,8,Fyear. Lord Timpson said he believes
OL,9,Fmore female offenders should serve
OL,10,Ftheir sentences in the community, and
OL,11,Freceive more 'wrap-around' support to
OL,12,Fprevent them going, or returning, to
OL,13,Fprison.
OL,15,F"What is very clear with female
OL,16,Foffenders is that a number of those
OL,17,Fwho are in prison when they leave
OL,18,Fprison need support when they're out.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
